1. Question: Identify bivalent peaks (H3K27me3 + H3K4me3) in mESC

library(ChIPpeakAnno)
#First i want to fuse the peaks together which characterize the bivalent peaks. It should be about 2100 peaks in the end. 

bivalent <- findOverlapPairs(k27me3, k4me3)
peaks_bi <- overlapsAny(p300, bivalent)
sum(peaks_bi)

#somehow the number seems to be way too small.
#gives me a locial output which can not be used to call bivalent peaks in the mESC data set somehow.
#So i tried to fuse the datasets of the histone marks together and then overlap the bivalent peaks

bivalent <- mergeByOverlaps(k4me3, k27me3)
p1 <- mergeByOverlaps(p300, bivalent)
p1 <- overlapsAny(p300, bivalent)
sum(p1)

#gave same amout of peaks which i think can not be true. As the upsetplot form above mentiones about 2100 overlaps of peaks for the three combined datasets.
